<div id="slide"><h1>Assignment: Style a Form</h1><h2>DUE: 2015-01-23</h2><h2>Submitted Status:  Date Submitted: Jan 23, 2015</h2><h2>Category: Homework, Weight: 6.25%</h2><h2>Folder Name: assignment1</h2><p>Link to your assignment (when you have it posted): </p><p class='firstLine'><a href='https://algoldma.w3.uvm.edu/cs142/assignment1/form.php' target='_blank'>https://algoldma.w3.uvm.edu/cs142/assignment1/form.php</a></p> <h1>Assignment #1: Styling a Form</h1> 

 <p><a href="peerCriteria.php?pid=22" target="_blank">Grading Criteria</a> NOTE: grading criteria subject to change until grading is open. Feel free to comment in class.</p>
<p><b>Part 1.</b> Create two sitemaps for the class. This file will be in a folder named cs142 which is on your UVM hosting account (we call it silk, or silk environment). See the guidelines are:
    <br><a href="http://www.sitemaps.org/protocol.html" target="_blank">http://www.sitemaps.org/protocol.html</a>
    <br><a href="https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/35769?hl=en" target="_blank">https://support.google.com/webmasters/answer/35769?hl=en</a></p>
<ol>
    <li>Create an xml sitemap.xml</li>
    <li>Create an html sitemap.php (or html).</li>
    <li>Include links to all your assignments.</li>
    <li>For each assignment be sure to add a new link to the current assignment due. For Example it should look something like this (We don't want to scroll to find the links):
        <br>
        <br><a href="https://rerickso.w3.uvm.edu/cs142" target="_blank">Example</a>
    </li>
     
</ol>


<hr> 

<p><b>Part 2.</b>Style this form</p>

<ol>
    <li>Clone on your desktop the git repository <a  target="_blank" href="https://github.com/Robert-Erickson/form-template-php">Web form template</a></li>
    <li>Name your style sheet (professional): form.css</li>
    <li>Create an alternative (see page 16) style sheet (creative): form2.css</li>
    <li>Add to the form (fieldset classes are for consistency when it is graded):<ol>
        <li>one text box for Last name (fieldset class="text") </li>
	<li>one list box, minimum of 5 options (fieldset class="lists").</li>
	<li>two check boxes (fieldset class="checkbox").</li>
	<li>at least one radio button group with at least two radio buttons (fieldset class="radio").</li>
	<li>Field sets and legends as needed (fieldset class="buttons", fieldset class="textarea").</li>
	<li>data should be validated for not missing, valid format etc as needed.</li>
	<li>current code the form submits to itself(do not change).</li>
        <li>current code form will be emailed to the person who filled it out (you can add a bcc to yourself).</li>
        <li>current code the form data will be saved to a csv file (you can change the name of the file)</li>
        <li>Be sure to modify the code so things like WRONG site are fixed.</li>
        </ol>
    </li>
    <li>Align the text for the labels.</li>
    <li>Have each label and input on the same line, do not have more than one text box on a line.</li> 
    <li>Align the text boxes etc so the form looks smooth (elements should line up with each other).</li>
    <li>Fix any broken borders (keep the border)</li>
    <li>Be sure to style the errors.</li>
    <li>You will be graded on the overall looks of your form.     
        
    </li>
    
    <!--<li>You can test your CSS by trying this link: (submitting your form from this site will not work so don't worry about that, we will have to go to your actual form)
        </li>-->
        
    <li>Always be sure all your pages:
	<ol>
            <li>have valid  html 5 (w3c.org standards).</li>
            <li>have valid  css 3 (w3c.org standards).</li>
        </ol>
    </li>
    
    <li>You will be graded on the quality of <a href="peerGrade.php"> your peer grading</a>. Peer grading needs to be completed in 48 hours from the due date.</li>
    
    
</ol>

